Next step is to  calculate the measures and calculated columns. Let us start with calculated columns, clik on Model and follow the steps as shown in the screenshot below:

2. GHG Emissions(Tonnes)

  1. Click on new column 
  2. Copy and paste the formula: GHG Emissions(Tonnes) = 'GHG Historical Emissions'[GHG Emissions]*1000000




3. GHG Emissions Per Capita:

In order to calculate the GHG Emissions per capita per country, we have to divide the Emissions emitted by the total population of the country. To do this, we have to use the LOOKUP function to look up the value of the population from our population table.

  1. Click on new column
  2. Copy and paste  : Population = LOOKUPVALUE('World Population'[Population],'World Population'[Country],'GHG Historical Emissions'[Country],'World Population'[Date],'GHG Historical Emissions'[Date])- As shown in the second screenshot, click on the population column and click on the comma - thousand seperator.                        Now w   hav       Now that we have our population column in our table, we can calculate our GHG Emissions per capita 
  3. Click on new columns
  4. Copy and paste the formula:  GHGE/Capita = DIVIDE('GHG Historical Emissions'[GHG Emissions(Tonnes)],'GHG Historical Emissions'[Population])



4. Measures:

Now let us create the measures. First create a table so we can store all our measures in one table. In the report view, click on ENTER DATA and name the table MyMeasures as shown in the GIF below


Right click on MyMeasures and select NEW MEASURE:

  • Total GHG Emissions(Tonnes)


  • Total GHG Emissions LY

 

  • YOY% GHG Emissions(Year over Year GHG Emissions):

Since this measure is a Year over Year, it should be represented in percentage. After creating this measure, click on it and

1. Go to  Measure tools

2.Change the format to Percentage

3.Change the decimal place to 1


  • Total GHGE/Capita


  • Total GHGE/Capita LY


  • YOY% GHGE/Capita(Year over Year GHG/Capita)


Since this measure is a Year over Year, it should be represented in percentage. After creating this measure, click on it and

1. Go to  Measure tools

2.Change the format to Percentage

3.Change the decimal place to 1


You can delete this column as shown below:
